      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Don't take Zolpidem along with melatonin; while both are taken for sleep, combining them significantly increases the risk of severe side effects like excessive drowsiness and the \"hangover\" effect the next day. Starting Zolpidem creates a complex medication management situation, so you should speak with your doctor immediately before taking either supplement alongside a new prescription. It is generally safer to discuss stopping the melatonin entirely or switching schedules with your healthcare provider to ensure you stay within prescribed dosages.",
      "source": "target",
