      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, combining Zolpidem with any amount of melatonin is unsafe because both drugs depress the central nervous system, leading to dangerous combinations of drowsiness and confusion regardless of the small melatonin dose. Even a tiny amount of natural melatonin can still interact chemically with your prescription, potentially causing unpredictable and severe side effects rather than simply speeding up sleep onset. Since you are already experiencing significant daytime impairment, your doctor needs to evaluate your specific dosage and safety profile before you try any new combinations.",
      "source": "target",
